@startuml
title dcm4chee-cdw Sequence: Receive DICOM Study to Publish CD/DVD with Label

actor "Modality / SCU" as Modality
participant "StoreSCP\n(StoreScpService)" as StoreSCP
participant "SpoolDir\n(SpoolDirService)" as SpoolDir
participant "Scheduler" as Scheduler
participant "MCR Emulator\n(MediaCreationRequestEmulatorService)" as Emulator
queue "JMS Queue\nMediaComposer" as QComposer
participant "MediaComposer\n(MediaComposerService)" as Composer
participant "Fileset Builder\n/ DicomDirDOM" as Fileset
queue "JMS Queue\nMakeIsoImage" as QIso
participant "MakeIsoImage\n(MakeIsoImageService)" as MkIso
participant "mkisofs" as Mkisofs
queue "JMS Queue\nPTPublish" as QPublish
participant "PTPublish\n(PTPublishService)" as Publish
collections "ISO Share\nptburn/iso" as IsoShare
collections "Label Share\nptburn/label" as LabelShare
collections "PTBurn Job Folder\nptburn/jobs" as JobFolder
collections "PTBurn Status Folder\nptburn/status" as StatusFolder
participant "PTBurn / Primera Publisher" as PTBurn

== Receive Study ==
Modality -> StoreSCP : C-STORE instances for study
StoreSCP -> SpoolDir : register and persist received instance files\nin cdw.spool archive buckets
SpoolDir --> StoreSCP : stored file locations
StoreSCP --> Modality : C-STORE-RSP success

== Detect and Create Media Request ==
Scheduler -> Emulator : poll()
Emulator -> SpoolDir : inspect received objects / emulate request files
SpoolDir --> Emulator : candidate study instances and trigger files
Emulator -> Emulator : build MediaCreationRequest\n(media writer = PTPublish, copies, fileset ID, volume ID)
Emulator -> QComposer : enqueue MediaCreationRequest

== Compose Fileset ==
QComposer -> Composer : deliver MediaCreationRequest
Composer -> Composer : initialize fileset root\nunder /data/fileset/<uid>
loop for each referenced SOP instance
  Composer -> SpoolDir : move/copy instance into fileset tree
  SpoolDir --> Composer : instance placed in fileset
end
Composer -> Fileset : build DICOMDIR and media directory structure
Fileset --> Composer : DICOMDIR written
Composer -> Fileset : create printable label content from study/patient metadata
Fileset -> LabelShare : write label file (PNG)
LabelShare --> Fileset : label path available
Fileset --> Composer : fileset ready
Composer -> QIso : enqueue updated MediaCreationRequest\n(filesetDir, labelFile)

== Create ISO Image ==
QIso -> MkIso : deliver MediaCreationRequest
MkIso -> MkIso : resolve ISO output path\n/data/iso/<filesetUid>.iso
MkIso -> Mkisofs : generate ISO from fileset directory
Mkisofs --> MkIso : ISO image created
MkIso -> IsoShare : write ISO file
IsoShare --> MkIso : ISO path available
MkIso -> QPublish : enqueue updated MediaCreationRequest\n(isoImageFile, labelFile)

== Publish to PTBurn ==
QPublish -> Publish : deliver MediaCreationRequest
Publish -> Publish : map local paths to shared paths\nImageFile -> \\HOST\ptburn\iso\...\nPrintLabel -> \\HOST\ptburn\label\...
Publish -> JobFolder : write JRQ file\nwith ImageFile, PrintLabel, copies, speed, verify, close-disc
JobFolder --> Publish : JRQ accepted

== Burn Disc and Print Label ==
PTBurn -> JobFolder : poll hot folder for new JRQ
PTBurn -> IsoShare : open ISO referenced by ImageFile
PTBurn -> LabelShare : open label referenced by PrintLabel
PTBurn -> PTBurn : burn CD/DVD and print disc label
PTBurn -> StatusFolder : write .don / .err and robot status files

== Completion ==
Publish -> StatusFolder : wait for completion status
StatusFolder --> Publish : job done or error details
Publish -> Publish : mark MediaCreationRequest done / failed

note over Composer,MkIso
Fileset stays internal to the container.
Only the ISO and label artifacts are shared out for PTBurn consumption.
end note

@enduml